            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>green beans</strong> to the reserved pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them), then bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter</strong> to a bowl and put in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 30 secs or until melted</p><p>Once melted, combine with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and your <strong>saffron</strong> – this is your <strong>smoky saffron butter</strong></p>",
